During validation testing, multiple malformed email inputs containing more than one “@” symbol 
were submitted (e.g., bontish@hor@fakemail.com and bandish@nt24@mroi.com). Both inputs were 
accepted by the system and allowed registration to proceed.

According to the stated email format requirements (single “@” symbol allowed), 
these inputs should have been rejected. This indicates a gap in email format validation on either 
the client side, server side, or both.

Further investigation is recommended to review the email validation logic and ensure 
enforcement of single “@” constraint.